You are implementing the render and stitch API routes (`app/api/pipeline/render/run/route.ts` and supporting routes) for a video production pipeline editor. These endpoints trigger Remotion section rendering and ffmpeg full-video stitching with parallel render support.

Requirements
1. `POST /api/pipeline/render/run` — accepts `{ sections?: string[] }`. Renders up to `project.json render.maxParallelRenders` sections concurrently using `lib/render.ts` `renderSection()`. Returns SSE stream with `{ jobId }`.
2. After each section renders, reads ffprobe duration via `getSectionDuration()` and updates `project.json` with `durationSeconds` and recalculated `offsetSeconds` for all sections.
3. `POST /api/pipeline/stitch/run` — runs ffmpeg concat via `stitchFullVideo()`. Returns `{ jobId }`.
4. `GET /api/pipeline/render/status` — returns `{ sections: SectionRenderStatus[], fullVideo: FullVideoInfo }`.
5. `SectionRenderStatus = { sectionId: string; status: 'done' | 'missing' | 'error'; duration?: number; progress?: number }`.
6. `FullVideoInfo = { exists: boolean; path?: string; size?: number; duration?: number }`.
7. No authentication required.

