Prompt Dependencies:
- types_TypeScript.prompt — provides `PipelineStage`, `RenderProgress`
- lib_jobs_TypeScript.prompt — provides `runPipelineStage`, `registerExecutor`
- lib_render_TypeScript.prompt — provides `renderSection`, `stitchFullVideo`, `getSectionDuration`
- lib_project_TypeScript.prompt — provides `loadProject`, `saveProject`

Instructions
- Parallel renders: use `Promise.all(batch.map(sectionId => renderSection(...)))` where batch size is `config.render.maxParallelRenders`.
- Section output path: `outputs/sections/{sectionId}.mp4`.
- Full video output: `outputs/full_video.mp4`.
- `offsetSeconds` recalculation: after all sections rendered, sort by section order, accumulate offsets as cumulative durations.
- Emit per-section progress events: `{ type: 'section-progress', sectionId, percent }`.
- Register executor: `registerExecutor('render', ...)`.
- `GET /api/pipeline/render/status`: check file existence in `outputs/sections/` for status detection.

Deliverable
- `app/api/pipeline/render/run/route.ts` — POST endpoint for section rendering.
- `app/api/pipeline/stitch/run/route.ts` — POST endpoint for full video stitching.
- `app/api/pipeline/render/status/route.ts` — GET endpoint for render status.

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- The Remotion bundle is pre-built; `renderSection` uses the existing bundle.
- `outputs/sections/` and `outputs/` directories are created as needed.

Please produce production-ready prompt content that will generate the module consistent with the above.
